review_blob: 5% ABV, 330ml bottle. Pours a light golden colour with a light white head. Strong malt finish with not much lingering bitterness.
6.6% ABV, 330ml bottle. Lovely honey golden colour with a light white head. Oak flavours very prominent with toffee on the nose.
500ml Bottle, 8.5 % ABV. Pours golden with light head that dissapates quite quickly. An enjoyable beer.
500ml Bottle, 5.0% ABV. Pours really dark with a good head. Was probably too cold when I drank it but overall, pretty good.
500ml Bottle, 4.8% ABV. Pours a deep golden colour with an off white head. Nice hit of maple on the mouth and a hood hop aroma.
330ml bottle, 8.5% ABV. Pours nice and dark with a tan head. Really good with no "hot" alcohol flavour.
500ml Bottle, 4.4% ABV. Pours amber with an off white head. I really enjoyed this one!
500ml Bottle 4.5% ABV. Pours amber with an off white head. Slight caramel after taste.
500ml Bottle, 3.8% ABV. Pours a golden colour with a good white head that dissapates quite quickly. Strong hop aroma that is not overpowering in the taste. An easy drinking ale.
440ml Bottle, 5 % ABV. Pours dark with a good beige head that fades. Good coffee nose but the flavour is overly bitter.
beer_name: Boston (South Africa) Black River Coffee Stout

review_blob: 550ml bottle, 5% ABV. Pours dark with an off white head that fades. Medicinal flavours that make it a tough drink.
550ml bottle, 4 % ABV. Nice spice notes on the nose. Pours light gold with awhite head that disappears quite quickly.
550ml bottle, 4% ABV. Pours with a deep amber colour and a small white head that fades quickly. Nice example of an Ale.
330ml bottle 10% ABV. No apparent "hot" flavour. A few sips in and you can feel it, but not taste it! A very nice Ale
500ml bottle, 4.5% ABV. Pours with a thin light brown head that fades quickly. Nice coffee notes.
500ml bottle, 4.7% ABV. Rich gold verging on amber with a white head that fades. Slight honey notes?
beer_name: Black Sheep Monty Pythons Holy Grail (Bottle)

review_blob: 440ml Bottle, 5% ABV. Nice golden colour with very good spice notes. Very refreshing!
A nice 5% ABV, but tastes a lot lighter. Good spice notes on the nose that translates nicely on the palate. No overpowering pumpkin flavour.
beer_name: Boston (South Africa) Van Hunks Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: 500ml bottle. Nice creamy head that is quite compact. Good chocolate flavour and aroma.
660ml bottle! Nice fruity aroma and lovely deep colour. All round nice example of the Ale.
A lot happening on the palate, no obvious "hot" flavour. Slight Chocolate aroma. Very good beer!
